The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 December is 134,528 (15,505.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 December, there were 7,093 new confirmed cases (817.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 December, there were 5,362 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 32% (1,731 extra cases).
